what is fair rent when living with a sister who owns the house mom had alzheimer's she moved in with my sister mom contributed per month when mom couldn't be alone at all i moved home from out of state to be full time caregiver i left my home in the care of my son i contributed per month we were like three peas in a pod mom lasted for slightly over two yrs i sold my home and opted to stay the question now is what is fair sister owns the home has the equity the tax deductions and the responsibility i rent a room and share the expenses the household bills including mortgage but not food comes to just under i contribute she cleans corners with q tips i blow off the dust she is a gourmet cook i'm content with cereal we differ on many things she commented that i would have to pay over for an efficiency apt she would like me to contribute more she can't afford house without me we need guidance so neither one feels resentful thank you so much this is a family issue not for strangers to decide Mortgage Flat tax Taxation in the United States Concurrent estate FairTax Housing cooperative United Kingdom corporation tax Rent (musical) Insurance Al Gore presidential campaign, 2000 Publicly funded medicine Stock Predatory lending Estoppel Life insurance Property tax Common Agricultural Policy Monopoly (game) Wal-Mart Shaggy dog story Social Security (United States) Annuity Tax deduction Corporation Tax EastEnders Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus Harlem Security (finance) Progressive tax Gross domestic product Money Real estate bubble Leasehold estate Supply-side economics Renting Food Stamp Program 401(k) National Kidney Foundation Singapore Homemaker Bond British residential property market Intellectual property Microeconomics Canadian and American health care systems compared Babylonian law 1957 World Series Capitalism Allodial title Fathers' rights Laura Schlessinger Infantilism Leasing Anarchism and capitalism Small business The Adventures of Pete & Pet